cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AR

This paper is primarily focused on the performance evaluation of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) on NVIDIA GPUs. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the algorithmic applications of NVIDIA GPU hardware specifics, which could also fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also introduces new FFT convolution implementations, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it discusses the performance of CNNs on GPU hardware.
